The paper discusses visual analytics applications and machine learning tasks, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on unsupervised clustering techniques suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of small data samples and user interpretation of results may also relate to information retrieval (cs.IR).
